- Khushil Sindhwad (Rating: 5): I like the place. The ambience gives me a vibe of 2000s brThe food and drinks are worth the money and the Caesars salad is the best in town.brDefinately a place for millennials to visit,the songs are also for the millennial generation to be enjoyed
- Janavi (Rating: 5): been to Matteo as a regular. just the perfect spot for having your personal time with some decent beverages and simple finger food. brThis place hosts seating that are well places, you can have the privacy you want and also have the comfort of personal space. brbrThe staff needs a mention. I have seen several worry about the service, I see no problem, and if I did face any, its just a matter of asking then for anything. Courteous staff, disciplined and considerate. it takes little to no effort to speak with kindness to anyone, show this to them, they will even have a smile on their face while serving to you. brover all...brambience- 4.5 because its spacious, points taken away because Id prefer it to be a little more lit up. brfood - 4.5 limited simple menu, points taken away because some of their menu has frozen items.brservice - 5 no complaints brwashroom hygiene - 4.0 can have better locks and better placement of tissues.brparking - available brbudget friendly and serves the purpose of a cafe.
- Kanishka Mehrotra (Rating: 5): The best place I found in Indranagar ,its become my go to cafe ,pasta burger shakes everything at its best,portion size is also really good as per the price, pasta is really creamy burger pattie is quite crunchy so loved the experience.br
- Harsha Gupta (Rating: 5): A beautiful cafe with really classy vibes, and one of my favorites especially for coffee.brNot just coffee, their various varities of Omlettes, Sandwiches, Pasta, Iced Tea everything is pretty perfect. Just love the vibes of this place, a perfect place for a leisure brunch or evening coffee. 
- Yamini Rahure (Rating: 5): I tried mostly all coffee, was really awesome taste and yeah you have to try chocolate drink. Surely you loved this place.
- Chandan Das (Rating: 5): Perfectly placed in mg road with a grand place to relax after a shopping spree. So well lit, funky ambience, and fairly priced.brWe had crossiant which was freshly baked and cold coffeebrAlso one more thing I liked, the prices mentioned in menu is inclusive of tax.
- Urmi Saha (Rating: 5): A place with very nice ambience to spend some leisure time in the evening. The chairs are very comfortable and deserve special mention. You can sit and work too in the comfortable sofas. The food is also very tasty. We had ordered hot chocolate, caramel coffee and club sandwich, and liked all of them a lot. Worth a visit if you want to spend some quality time with friends or your date over coffee.
- Jayita De (Rating: 5): Coffe and food are both great. Atmosphere is ideal and service also very good. Definitely must visit cafe in Bangalore.
- Adarsh Bakshi (Rating: 5): Try the shekerato! An eternal bliss. Their white chocolate is a must try in any form. The food is simple and tasty. A good place for both business and romantic discussions
- Pranav Nandan (Rating: 5): I visit this place quite often. The ambience is good and pocket friendly, especially on Christmas the coffee Americano was really smooth. Added some pics.

Reviews:
- Rhea Fernandes (Rating: 5): amazing food!
- Janhavi Jayakumar (Rating: 5): Really good food, the service is even better, the bakery goods takes you back to Southeast Asia in seconds, the milo classic milkshake was nice trip back to childhood.
- Aakash Shweta (Rating: 5): If you have experienced Singapores hawker stalls and malaysian food, kopitiam lahs food will take your mind and soul right back to it.brbrDo not expect Indianized asian food, they provide authentic for real malay food only. brbrTotally worth it.brbrMust tries  Hainanese Chicken Rice  Char Siu
- Aparajita Rao Das (Rating: 5): The char kway teow reminded us of the Singapore Hawker stall. brEven though the menu is limited , all the items we ordered was really good.brWe had the curry puff, prawn hargow malaysian fried chicken and the sea food char kway teow. brIn drinks, the pandan cold brew was quite a different experience, sour guava lemonade is a must try and tropical tango was a fresh fruit juice melange. brThe service was a bit slow and there is some room for improvement there. brThe place is pricey but worth it. brbrWe had done the reservations about a week ahead , walk ins will be tough.
- Dibya (Rating: 5): Great food and drinks. The fried chicken, char kway Teo, dimsums and curry puffs were all delicious. our drinks were good too. standout was the guava lemonade. The pandan cold brew and the tropical mocktail were good too. recommend the place.
- Sunshine Basumatary (Rating: 5): Something different from the usual lot ! The food and beverages were nice in middle of a relaxed seating ! No harsh music which i am annoyed mostly at, the services was quick. The winner was the tiramisu !
- Zaynio Kadete (Rating: 5): Really love the place, enjoy my dinner and servant was on point , highly recommend
- Achuth Pv (Rating: 5): food is Malaysian. tastes malaysian. place feels malayaian
- Sanjana (Rating: 5): The food here is absolutely perfect. The authentic Malaysian flavours really come through. The kopi coffee is slightly strong and watery, but thats exactly how I like my coffee. The Malaysian sweet platter was wonderful too- not too sweet.
- Ayesha Cassim (Rating: 5): The Otik Otik was the stand out dish for us, absolutely delicious!
